result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Roger Steven Miller was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Apprs: CO: SRN, Rpr: Kasten, Clerk: Evenson. ADA:  Matthew L Hartung DF ATTY:  Barry Curtis Lundeen DF: Roger Steven Miller appeared. Case called at 11:08. ADA Hartung updates the court there is a DJOC agreement on count 1 only. Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads NC to Ct 1  in 14CF417 and G to Ct. 2 in 14CF417. DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Court confirms the obstruction was at the home in North Hudson. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of Ct 1 and defers the entry of conviction and guilty of Ct 2 in 14CF417. Sentencing arguments. DE makes statement. Crt orders: 
- Costs of $243
- NO DNA sample ordered. 

Court orders DE to meet with the diversion program coordinator by 12 tomorrow. 
Court orders the diversion program coordinator to provide quarterly updates. Clerk to set for review around Nov. 15, 2016.
